            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I'd like to take this opportunity to advocate for a particular use case: highlighting listchars *only* in visual mode. This is a feature that is implemented and turned on in VS Code by default and which they got from Sublime. I have a plugin, [visual-whitespace.nvim](https://github.com/mcauley-penney/visual-whitespace.nvim), that implements this feature and has a modest amount of popularity, but it is an established feature in other text editors and might have a place in Vim.\n\nTo implement it, we would have to be able to make listchars invisible in normal mode but highlighted in visual, meaning two new highlight groups. The new 'NormalListChars` group could be linked to whatever group is used for listchars right now to prevent breaking color schemes. This would fulfill OP's original ask, but also extend it by providing more room for customization without breaking existing functionality.",
